    • Method Detail

      • setTime

        public void setTime()
        This method is to count down. Time starts with 5 minutes and 60 seconds. That means player has 6 minutes for whole game. Seconds starts with 60 and down to 0. Minutes starts with 5. If seconds reach 00, minutes will reduce by 1 and seconds will set to 60 again. if minutes reach 0, system will redirect to end automatically.

      • calScore

        public int calScore(int calScore,
                    int calMins)
        This method will run if user finish the game. Calculate the final score and pass the score to updateScore()
        Parameters:
        calScore - get the user scored score
        calMins - get the remain time
        Returns:
        final score by calScore * calMins, result will store in finalScore

      • updateScore

        public void updateScore()
        This method is call the setScore() method in RMIInterface. finalsScore and the player's username will pass in to the setScore() method.

      • finalStage

        public void finalStage()
        This is to proceed final stage of the game. If player finish the game by complete all the round or because of use all the attempts, this method will run. calScore() and updateScore() methods will run in this method.

      • setMax

        public void setMax()
        This will select top 5 players from the database table and show in the table in main interface.

      • number

        public void number()
        This will generate random number from the external web API and that number will show in the game. System will pass minimum and maximum value to the APi and, API will return randomly generated number between passed minimum and maximum values.

      • userInputs

        public void userInputs()
        This method is to take user inputs and validate the answers of the user.

      • btnNextActionPerformed

        private void btnNextActionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent evt)
        This method will run when player click next button after fill all the text fields. This checks whether the validation of the answers in userInput() is the same as the random number generated by the external web API. Attempts and levels are calculated in this method. finalStage() will call if user finish all the attempts or all the rounds.
        Parameters:
        evt - Action event

      • btnExitActionPerformed

        private void btnExitActionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent evt)
        If user click on EXIT button while playing the game, system will prompt warning message. If user clicks yes system will close, else if user clicks no, user can continue the game
        Parameters:
        evt - Action Event
